{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"convenience"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"?("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"id"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"flags"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ApplicationFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO16ApplicationFlagsV"},{"kind":"text","text":" = [])"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using #GtkApplication, it is not necessary to call gtk_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"manually. It is called as soon as the application gets registered as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the primary instance."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Concretely, gtk_init() is called in the default handler for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"#GApplication::startup signal. Therefore, #GtkApplication subclasses should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"chain up in their #GApplication::startup handler before using any GTK+ API."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that commandline arguments are not passed to gtk_init()."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"All GTK+ functionality that is available via commandline arguments"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can also be achieved by setting suitable environment variables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_DEBUG"},{"type":"text","text":", so this should not be a big"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"problem. If you absolutely must support GTK+ commandline arguments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can explicitly call gtk_init() before creating the application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If non-%NULL, the application ID must be valid.  See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"g_application_id_is_valid()."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If no application ID is given then some features (most notably application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uniqueness) will be disabled. A null application ID is only allowed with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GTK+ 3.6 or later."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/application\/init(id:flags:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/Application\/init(id:flags:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new #GtkApplication instance."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"init(id:flags:)","roleHeading":"Initializer","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"convenience"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"?("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"id"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"flags"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ApplicationFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO16ApplicationFlagsV"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"symbolKin